Tetraplegia, paralysis of all 4 limbs, is usually the result of cervical spinal 
cord injury. Recovery of independence is the primary goal of people with 
tetraplegia; this requires reconstruction of upper extremity function. Active 
elbow extension, necessary for a wide range of activities of daily living, is 
